KAlarm

KAlarm provides a graphical interface for setting up personal alarm/reminder
messages. The messages pop up on the screen at the time you specify.

KAlarm also provides a command line interface. Other programs can also use
DCOP calls to execute functions.

See the INSTALL file for installation instructions.


USE ON NON-KDE DESKTOPS

For details on the requirements for setting up KAlarm to run on non-KDE
desktops, see the INSTALL file.


